# Styling Rules

## Tailwind bd- Prefix (MANDATORY)

Every Tailwind utility class requires the `bd-` prefix. This is configured in `tailwind.config.ts`.

```tsx
// Correct
<div className="bd-flex bd-items-center bd-gap-2 bd-bg-background bd-text-foreground">

// Wrong — classes will NOT apply
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 bg-background text-foreground">
```

### Variants with prefix

```tsx
// Correct: variant BEFORE prefix
"hover:bd-bg-primary/90"
"dark:bd-text-foreground"
"md:bd-grid-cols-2"
"focus-visible:bd-ring-2"

// Wrong: prefix before variant
"bd-hover:bg-primary/90"
```

## CSS Variables (HSL Format)

Colors are defined as HSL values in `src/globals.css`:

```css
:root { --background: 0 0% 100%; }
.dark { --background: 0 0% 3.9%; }
```

Used in Tailwind as `hsl(var(--name))`. Do NOT use hex (#fff) or RGB directly.

When adding custom colors:
1. Define CSS variable in `src/globals.css` (both `:root` and `.dark`)
2. Map in `tailwind.config.ts` under `theme.extend.colors`

## shadcn/ui Components

- Located in `src/components/ui/` (flat structure, no subdirectories)
- Install: `pnpm dlx shadcn-ui add <component>` (auto-applies bd- prefix via `components.json`)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging

## Domain Component Structure

```
src/components/{domain}/
├── index.ts    # Barrel export — ONLY public API
├── ui/         # React components
├── model/      # Hooks, stores
├── types/      # .d.ts files
├── consts/     # Constants
└── lib/        # Utilities
```

Import from domain root only: `import { X } from '@/components/{domain}'`
